cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless ad hoc networks and proposes a novel scheduling scheme to improve spatial capacity. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses signal-to-interference-ratio (SIR) threshold to optimize the scheduling scheme, which is a common technique in information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is a possible category as the paper deals with the interference induced coupling in the decisions of transmitters, which can be viewed as a multi-agent system. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a control scheme to optimize the probing and data transmission in the network. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with data transmission in wireless networks, which can be related to multimedia applications.
